The paper discusses deep learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The focus is on understanding the geometric principles behind deep learning, which suggests that it may fall under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces concepts related to neural networks and probability distributions, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper proposes the application of optimal mass transportation theory, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
